PRESS NOTE,
There have so far been within the Council of
Ministers three classes of Ministers, namely Cabinet
Ministers, Ministers of state and Deputy Ministers.
The recent re-designation of the sentor Ministers as
Ministers of Cabinet rank, who are Members of the
Cabinet, and Ministers of Cabinet rank, who are not
Mam ber s of the Cabinet, does not involve an increa se
in this number or any other change. A MO1ster of the
latter category, if appointed to assist a Member of
the Cabinet in the administration of a Ministry, is
described as a Minister of State for that Ministry to
aistinguish him from the senior Minister in charge of
that Ministry. Tho se described as Ministers of State,
